      "Based on the search results, I found information about AI IDEs including Windsurf and Cursor, but **no specific results about a new AI IDE launched in February 2025**. Here's what I found:\n\n## Key AI IDE Landscape in 2025\n\n### Main Players Mentioned:\n\n1. **Cursor**\n   - Launched by Anysphere (founded by MIT students in 2022)\n   - Valuation reached ~$90 billion by May 2025\n   - Pricing: $20/month Pro plan\n   - Known for: Deep codebase context, Agent mode, multi-file refactoring\n\n2. **Windsurf** (by Codeium)\n   - **Launched November 2024** (not February 2025)\n   - Pricing: $10-15/month (more affordable than Cursor)\n   - Known for: \"Deep Context\" understanding, smooth UI, competitive pricing\n   - First to introduce Agent mode (November 14, 2024)\n\n3. **Antigravity** (by Google)\n   - **Launched December 2025** (according to one source)\n   - Features Gemini 3 and Claude 4.5 models\n   - Currently **free**\n   - Strong Agent capabilities with built-in browser integration\n\n4. **Trae** (Chinese AI IDE)\n   - Permanently free for domestic version\n   - International version: $10/month after first month\n   - Gained traction in Q3 2025\n\n### What I Did NOT Find:\n- **No specific AI IDE launch mentioned for February 2025**\n- The closest launches were:\n  - Windsurf: November 2024\n  - Antigravity: December 2025 (conflicting timeline)\n  - Various feature rollouts and updates throughout 2025\n\n### Recommendation:\nThe search results may not have captured a very recent or niche AI IDE launch from February 2025. You might want to:\n- Search more specifically with the exact product name if you know it\n- Check developer communities like Reddit (r/programming, r/devtools) or Hacker News\n- Look at official announcements from major tech companies\n\nWould you like me to search for any specific AI IDE name or clarify details about what you're looking for?"
