round $15/month for Pro version\n\n## **Other Major AI IDEs from Early 2025:**\n\n### **Trae 3.0 (ByteDance)**\n- **Release:** Early 2025 (version 3.0)\n- **Developer:** ByteDance\n- **Key Features:**\n  - Positioned as an \"Adaptive AI IDE\"\n  - SOLO mode for fully autonomous coding\n  - Free access to Claude/GPT-4 models\n  - Optimized for Chinese users\n  - 600K+ global users, 1.6M monthly active users\n\n### **Other Notable AI IDEs Active in 2025:**\n- **Cursor** - VS Code fork, AI-native design ($20/month)\n- **GitHub Copilot** - Deep GitHub ecosystem integration ($10/month)\n- **Zed** - High-performance Rust-based with AI assistance\n- **PearAI** - Open-source Cursor alternative\n\n## **Market Context:**\n\nThe search results indicate that **February-April 2025** was a significant period for AI IDE development, with multiple sources calling 2025 \"a watershed year for AI coding tools\" and marking the transition from \"AI Assistant 1.0\" to \"Agentic Coding 3.0.\"\n\n**Note:** The exact \"full AI IDE\" specifically launched in February 2025 isn't explicitly named in the search results, but Windsurf's major Netlify integration announcement came in early April 2025, and Trae had significant version 3.0 updates in early 2025.\n\n\nREMINDER: You MUST include the sources above in your response to the user using markdown hyperlinks."
