rategy=&tbkt=J&uid=\"},{\"title\":\"Claude Code 发布一周年：2026年Agentic AI底层基础设施与标准化\",\"url\":\"https://blog.csdn.net/sD7O95O/article/details/158398776\"},{\"title\":\"ai-team · GitHub Topics\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/topics/ai-team\"},{\"title\":\"Agent Client Protocol (ACP)\",\"url\":\"http://www.jetbrains.com.cn/acp/\"},{\"title\":\"QwenLM/Qwen3.5 - GitHub\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/QwenLM/Qwen3.5\"},{\"title\":\"OpenAI Codex CLI 完整速查表：命令、配置、MCP 一网打尽\",\"url\":\"https://blog.csdn.net/zhq426/article/details/158006075\"}]\n\nBased on my search, I found several AI coding CLI and terminal agents that were released or significantly updated in February 2026. However, I wasn't able to find specific \"Show HN\" posts on Hacker News. Here are the notable AI coding CLI/terminal agent releases from February 2026:\n\n## **Major AI Coding CLI/Terminal Releases - February 2026**\n\n### 1. **OpenCode** (February 10, 2026)\n- **95,000+ GitHub stars** - An open-source AI coding tool with native Terminal UI\n- Supports **75+ models** including Claude, OpenAI, Gemini, and local models\n- Compatible with **Agent Client Protocol (ACP)** - a new standard for AI agent communication\n- Multi-session support and broad model compatibility\n- [Source: InfoQ report](https://www.infoq.com/news/2026/02/opencode-coding-agent/)\n\n### 2. **Qwen Code CLI** (February 17, 2026)\n- Part of **Qwen 3.5 release** by Alibaba's Qwen team\n- Open-source AI agent specifically designed for terminal use\n- Optimized for Qwen models with support for development workflows\n- Implements the Agent Client Protocol\n- [GitHub: QwenLM/Qwen3.5](https://github.com/QwenLM/Qwen3.5)\n\n### 3. **Solon Code CLI** (February 22, 2026)\n- A **Java-based implementation** of Claude Code CLI\n- Described as a domestic (Chinese) open-source alternative\n- Supports terminal conversation, code generation, project structure understanding\n- [Reported on Chinese developer blogs](https://www.cnblogs.com/)\n\n### 4. **OpenClaw (formerly Clawdbot & Moltbot)** - Ongoing Development\n- **190,000+ GitHub stars** as of February 2026\n- Open-source ecosystem focused on CLI-based AI agent toolkits\n- Terminal CLI, IDE integrations, and Web UI available\n- Active community with \"ClawHub\" for agent skills\n- [OpenClaw Guide](https://milvus.io/zh-hant/blog/openclaw-formerly-clawdbot-moltbot-explained-a-complete-guide-to-the-autonomous-ai-agent.md)\n\n### 5. **AionUI** (v1.8.8 - February 12, 2026)\n- Multi-AI Agent desktop tool (15.2k stars)\n- Provides unified GUI for CLI tools like Gemini CLI and Claude Code\n- Supports remote access, scheduling, and intelligent file management\n- [GitHub: iOfficeAI/AionUi](https://github.com/iOfficeAI/AionUi)\n\n## **Industry Context - February 2026**\n\nThe search results indicate that **2026 is being called the \"Year of CLI\"** for AI coding agents, with several key trends:\n\n- **Paradigm shift** from IDE-based completion to terminal-based agentic execution\n- **Agent Client Protocol (ACP)** emerging as a standard for agent-IDE communication\n- Major players: **Claude Code, OpenAI Codex CLI, Gemini CLI, GitHub Copilot CLI, Qwen Code**\n- Focus on **agentic capabilities** - autonomous task execution rather than just code completion\n\nWhile I couldn't locate specific \"Show HN\" posts, these tools represent the state-of-the-art in AI coding CLI/terminal agents from February 2026. Would you like me to search for more specific information about any of these tools?\n\n\nREMINDER: You MUST include the sources above in your response to the user using markdown hyperlinks."
