### Repository:\n- **GitHub**: https://github.com/anomalyco/opencode/ (some sources also mention sst/opencode)\n- **Official Site**: https://opencode.ai\n\n### Key Features:\n1. **Terminal-First Design**: Native Terminal UI (TUI) experience\n2. **Multi-Model Support**: Compatible with 75+ models including:\n   - Claude\n   - OpenAI\n   - Google Gemini\n   - Various local models\n   - GLM-4.7 (mentioned in setup guides)\n3. **Dual Agent Modes**:\n   - \"build\" mode: Full permissions development agent\n   - \"plan\" mode: Read-only analysis agent (safer, requires explicit authorization)\n4. **Cross-Platform Support**:\n   - CLI tool\n   - Desktop applications (macOS, Windows, Linux)\n   - VS Code and Cursor plugins\n5. **Protocol Support**: Agent Client Protocol (ACP) for standardizing IDE/AI agent communication\n\n### Why It's Popular:\n- **Zero Cost**: Free alternative to GitHub Copilot ($10/month) and Cursor ($10-20/month)\n- **Open Source**: Hundreds of contributors\n- **Flexible**: Works with existing paid services like ChatGPT Plus/Pro and GitHub Copilot\n- **Production-Ready**: Focuses on being deployable and production-ready infrastructure\n\nThe project is positioned as a leading open-source alternative to commercial AI coding assistants, specifically targeting developers who want enterprise-level AI programming capabilities without subscription costs.\n\n\nREMINDER: You MUST include the sources above in your response to the user using markdown hyperlinks."
